6: We only need to deliver a letter?
9:
Yes. We were asked to deliver it to 
a mansion over that way.
13:
Surely, there must have been better 
quests than this.
19:
Beggars can't be choosers. We're low 
on gold, so we have to take whatever 
puts bread on the table.
34:
I know it's not the most exciting job, 
but it should be easy enough and the 
pay is surprisingly good.
35:
Can you believe we're getting 
a hundred gold for this?
38: Wait—Did you just say a HUNDRED?
41: Yup! I couldn't believe it either!
45:
There is NO good reason for a delivery 
this simple to cost that much. Were 
they in that much of a hurry?
48:
There's no rush, but... Doesn't it look 
like a love letter? I think he was too 
embarrassed to deliver it himself.
53:
Hmm. Even so, a hundred gold is far 
too much. This letter may be more 
trouble than it's worth.
56: No way! Why would it be—
59:
Hey! You there! What are you doing 
here?
64:
Yes, you. I'm with the Guild. Name's 
Dermot.
65:
Now why don't you explain what 
adventurers such as yourselves are 
doing in this part of town?
68: We're here to deliver a love letter to—
77:
Veeery interesting. You see, we've 
been hearing reports of a shady fellow 
bothering ladies 'round here.
80:
That wouldn't be YOU, now would it? 
I think we need to have a niiice long 
chat back at the Guild.
85:
Look at us! Do you really think WE 
would run around accosting women? 
We're just delivering a letter.
88:
You never know! Now shut up and 
hand over the letter!
97:
Hey! Keep your hands away from 
them! Is THIS the Guild's idea of 
justice?!
102:
Now, now, let's all calm down, 
shall we?
107:
Shion! You know, the information 
broker? Haven't you heard of me?
111:
Huh? Now that you mention it, he 
DOES look a little familiar...
114:
Hmph! This is none of your business, 
gossip-monger.
118:
Oh, but it IS! See, the lovely lady down 
the road has got herself caught up in 
QUITE the scandal, the poor darling!
121:
She's an actress—the Queen of the 
Stage! Unfortunately for her though, 
two local gentlemen are vying to be 
her Prince Charming.
123:
It's a full-on feud, but get this! A little 
birdie told me one of them's been 
skulking around her neighborhood. 
Isn't that right?
128:
I do believe I introduced myself as an 
information broker, didn't I? I'm saying 
I've got goods you might be interested
in.
130:
For example, dirt on the other guy 
involved in the scandal.
133:
It'd be a shame if word got out that 
the Guild was shaking down errand 
boys. Forget the kids over there—Why 
don't you come with me?
138:
You lot are free to go. Don't do 
anything else suspicious, you hear?
139:
And make sure you dispose of that 
letter!
143:
My heart goes out to the poor actress 
who got dragged into all of this. 
She must feel so betrayed!
146:
I know all of this city's juiciest secrets. 
I wouldn't mind sharing with the Guild. 
I think we'd make great business 
partners!
152:
Oh! I just remembered where I've seen 
that Shion guy!
155:
He had a hood on when I saw him,
so I didn't recognize him at first, but 
he's the one who hired me to deliver 
the letter!
158: I just KNEW it was too good to be true.
162:
Let's open the letter. We should check 
its contents.
167:
Thanks for the help, kid! I'd be more 
careful if I were you, though. Did you 
really think someone would pay that 
much for a letter?
169:
P.S. If you're ever in the market for 
intel, I can hook you up!
176:
Do we still get paid? We're out of food
—and funds.
182:
I doubt it. Looks like we're fresh out of 
luck, too.
